# .env.example — local environment for crypto-order-book
#
# This app intentionally consumes NO build-time / client env vars.
# There are deliberately no VITE_* variables: baking env-specific values into
# the bundle would break the build-once-promote CD model (one artifact is built
# once and promoted DEV -> UAT -> PROD unchanged). If you came here looking for
# where env-specific config lives, it is NOT here.
#
# Environment-specific config (env name, API base URL, WebSocket URL) is
# delivered at RUNTIME via /config.js -> window.__APP_CONFIG__, read through
# getConfig() in src/lib/app-config.ts:
#   - dev      -> hardcoded in the runtimeConfig plugin (vite.config.ts)
#   - deployed -> per-env `vars` in wrangler.jsonc, served by worker/config-response.ts
#
# Worker *secrets* (for a future backend) do NOT go here either — copy
# .dev.vars.example -> .dev.vars for those. See the "Secrets" section of README.md.
#
# There is nothing to copy today; this file is a signpost. Add a real build-time
# variable here only if one is ever genuinely needed (none is today).
